This paper is about optimization techniques for black-box functions, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on combining Bayesian optimization and Lipschitz optimization, which are both popular techniques in this area. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves some theoretical analysis and experiments, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
